==English==
{{wikipedia|Bunny Boiler}}
===Etymology===
From the 1987 film [[w:Fatal Attraction|Fatal Attraction]], in which a character exacts revenge on an ex-lover by killing his daughter's pet rabbit, and leaving it boiling on the stove to be found by his family.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[bunny]] [[boiler]]}}

# An excessively [[obsessive]] girlfriend (or less commonly, boyfriend), especially one who reacts in an extreme way to the ending of a relationship.

